        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "You can't disable the locale detection in Zend_Validate_Iban when using a Zend_Config (xml).\r\n\r\nIn xml you need to specify false with a zero.\r\n{code:xml}\r\n<validators>\r\n  <iban>\r\n    <validator>Iban<\/validator>\r\n    <options>\r\n      <locale>0<\/locale>\r\n    <\/options>\r\n    <\/iban>\r\n<validators>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nbut because the validator checks also the type, you can't disable it.\r\n{code}\r\n  if ($locale !== false) {\r\n    \/* some code *\/\r\n  }\r\n{code}\r\nIt works for me by changing the controle to (without type checking)\r\n{code}\r\n  if ($locale != false) {\r\n    \/* some code *\/\r\n  }\r\n{code}"
        },
